OL,5,Ctrust
OL,7,F"They'd been told, they've been warned
OL,8,Fthat she wasn't of the right frame of
OL,9,Fmind. They said, 'don't worry, we'll
OL,10,Fup her obs(ervations), we'll keep
OL,11,Fsomeone with her. We'll keep a good
OL,12,Feye on her'.
OL,14,F"And later on, I got a phone call to
OL,15,Fsay she's in hospital. You need to get
OL,16,Fthere now."
OL,18,FChristie's grandmother Casey Tremain
OL,19,Fremembers the horror unfolding.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/23
